Discovery of a predaceous drosophilid Acletoxenus indicus Malloch in South China, with descriptions of the taxonomic, ecological and molecular characters (Diptera: Drosophilidae)A drosophilid, Acletoxenus indicus Malloch, with larvae preying on Aleurodicus dispersus and Aleurocanthus sp. (Hemiptera: Aleyrodidae), is discovered from Guangdong and Hainan Provinces, China, and its morphological, ecological and molecular characters are described.